questions.ask: This ancient structure is the only manmade object that can be seen from space
questions.answer: The Great Wall of China

questions.ask: According to some myths, this ancient structure was the birth place of all the world`s languages
questions.answer: The Tower of Babel

questions.ask: The Statue of Liberty has three references to this ancient statue
questions.answer: The Colossus of Rhodes
questions.note: The Statue of Liberty is the same height, has solar rays on her head, and the poem she carries refers to the Colossus

questions.ask: The Great Pyramid at Giza points directly at this constellation
questions.answer: Orion

questions.ask: The shadow of a serpent crawls up it every equinox
questions.answer: The Temple of Kukulcan
questions.note: The Feathered shadow of Kukulcan, or Quetzalcoatl can be seen at the rising and setting of the sun along the side of the North staircase

questions.ask: This underworld goddess was returned to the land of the living due to the extremity of her mother`s mourning
questions.answer: Persephone

questions.ask: He was also a god of crops, minerals and prosperity as well as the Underworld
questions.answer: Hades

questions.ask: If your heart weighs as evil, Anubis would feed it to her
questions.answer: Ammit

questions.ask: These 10 Chinese underworld rulers judge the fate of a soul after death
questions.answer: The Yama-Kings

questions.ask: Inanna was forced to strip naked in order to visit her realm
questions.answer: Erishkigal

questions.ask: This mythical utopia is rumored to be hidden in the Kunlun Mountains
questions.answer: Shangri-La

questions.ask: Juan Ponce de León died in his quest to discover this
questions.answer: The Fountain of Youth

questions.ask: This place was believed to lie on the floor of the Indian Ocean
questions.answer: Lemuria

questions.ask: This Mystical Isle was also known for its apples
questions.answer: Avalon

questions.ask: Some scholars believe that references to this mythical city actually were a reference to a person instead of a place
questions.answer: El Dorado

questions.ask: This Horn of Plenty, filled with the bounty of the season is associated with Mabon
questions.answer: The Cornucopia

questions.ask: This fire festival marks the mid point between winter and summer
questions.answer: Imbolc

questions.ask: This Sabbat occurs at the same time of year as the Roman festival of Floralia
questions.answer: Beltane

questions.ask: This Sabbat is named after the Celtic deity who by legend established it in honor of his foster mother
questions.answer: Lughnassadh

questions.ask: In 1643 the British Parliament abolished this heathen holiday
questions.answer: Yule

questions.ask: This brew is made from fermented honey
questions.answer: Mead

questions.ask: This Olympian brew was reputed to grant immortality
questions.answer: Ambrosia

questions.ask: Egypt was spared when Sekhmet was tricked into drinking this
questions.answer: Beer colored red with ochre

questions.ask: He was the first recorded in the Old Testament to make alcohol
questions.answer: Noah

questions.ask: This ancient Babylonian law code included laws regulating beer and beer parlors
questions.answer: The Code of Hammurabi

questions.answer: Mercury

questions.answer: Diana

questions.ask: Some say he was born from a silver egg and had two types of arrows
questions.answer: Cupid

questions.ask: The sun of Somnus, he was the God of Dreams
questions.answer: Morheus

questions.ask: They were the personification of charm and beauty in nature and in human life
questions.answer: Gratiae

questions.ask: This method merely requires any deck of cards
questions.answer: Cartomancy
questions.note: Tarot is the most common form of Cartomancy

questions.ask: This method always requires a campfire, candle, or some other form of flame
questions.answer: Pyromancy

questions.ask: Using sticks, stones and bones to cast lots can be used to tell the future with this
questions.answer: Cleromancy

questions.ask: This method of divination involves reading the outcome from tossed arrows
questions.answer: Belomancy

questions.ask: This method revolves around the reading of tea leaves
questions.answer: Tasseomancy

questions.ask: Heracles wear the skin of this creature
questions.answer: The Nemean Lion

questions.ask: Its blood is prophesied to be the poison that will kill Thor
questions.answer: Jörmungandr

questions.ask: Every nine years seven of Athens` finest youths and fairest maidens were delivered to him
questions.answer: The Minotaur

questions.ask: He was responsible for eclipses when he managed to swallow Ra`s Sun Boat
questions.answer: Who is Apophis

questions.ask: This Japanese demon's most distinguishing feature is a circular depression on top of its head that must remain filled with water lest he die
questions.answer: Kappa

questions.ask: This 15th tome was used to identify a witch
questions.answer: Malleus Maleficarum

questions.ask: This French woman was executed for crimes including Witchcraft, Heresy, and dressing in the manner of a man
questions.answer: Joan of Arc

questions.ask: This Salem man's last words were reputed to be "More Weight"
questions.answer: Giles Corey

questions.ask: He issued the Papal Bull disbanding the prosecuted Order of the Knights Templar
questions.answer: Pope Clement V

questions.ask: In 1573 he was executed for witchcraft, lycanthropy, and "eating meat on a Friday"
questions.answer: Gilles Garnier

questions.ask: This is the first Sunday after the full moon after the spring equinox
questions.answer: When is Easter

questions.ask: What three signs of the Zodiac are associated with water
questions.answer: Cancer, Scorpio, and Pisces

questions.ask: In Tarot, this energy is at the beginning of the cycle of three
questions.answer: Cardinal

questions.ask: This one of the seven magical tools is used to incite Astral Projection
questions.answer: Scourge

questions.ask: The tenth Sephirah of the Tree of Life, it receives influences from the others
questions.answer: Malkuth
